segment.source: How to Register and Unregister a Publishing Server by Using the Management Console
segment.target: How to Register and Unregister a Publishing Server by Using the Management Console

segment.source: You can register and unregister publishing servers that will synchronize with the App-V 5.1 management server.
segment.target: You can register and unregister publishing servers that will synchronize with the App-V 5.1 management server.

segment.source: You can also see the last attempt that the publishing server made to synchronize the information with the management server.
segment.target: You can also see the last attempt that the publishing server made to synchronize the information with the management server.

segment.source: Use the following procedure to register or unregister a publishing server.
segment.target: Use the following procedure to register or unregister a publishing server.

segment.source: To register a publishing server using the Management Console
segment.target: To register a publishing server using the Management Console

segment.source: Connect to the Management Console and select Servers.
segment.target: Connect to the Management Console and select Servers.

segment.source: For more information about how to connect to the Management Console, see How to Connect to the Management Console.
segment.target: For more information about how to connect to the Management Console, see How to Connect to the Management Console.

segment.source: A list of publishing servers that already synchronize with the management server is displayed.
segment.target: A list of publishing servers that already synchronize with the management server is displayed.

segment.source: Click Register New Server to register a new server.
segment.target: Click Register New Server to register a new server.

segment.source: Type a computer name of a domain joined computer on the Server Name line, to specify a name for the server.
segment.target: Type a computer name of a domain joined computer on the Server Name line, to specify a name for the server.

segment.source: You should also include a domain name, for example, MyDomainTestServer.
segment.target: You should also include a domain name, for example, MyDomainTestServer.

segment.source: Click Check.
segment.target: Click Check.

segment.source: Select the computer and click Add to add the computer to the list of servers.
segment.target: Select the computer and click Add to add the computer to the list of servers.

segment.source: The new server will be displayed in the list.
segment.target: The new server will be displayed in the list.

segment.source: To unregister a publishing server using the Management Console
segment.target: To unregister a publishing server using the Management Console

segment.source: Connect to the Management Console and select Servers.
segment.target: Connect to the Management Console and select Servers.

segment.source: For more information about how to connect to the Management Console, see How to Connect to the Management Console.
segment.target: For more information about how to connect to the Management Console, see How to Connect to the Management Console.

segment.source: A list of publishing servers that synchronize with the management server is displayed.
segment.target: A list of publishing servers that synchronize with the management server is displayed.

segment.source: To unregister the server, right-click the computer name and select the computer name and select unregister server.
segment.target: To unregister the server, right-click the computer name and select the computer name and select unregister server.
